In wise foresight, because most of its 90 staff members are in baby boom age, and the company is anxious that the project-goers and architects return to their jobs as soon as possible.
Along with the possibility of working shorter, the kindergarten is another bonus that Arch.Design has to offer to its employees in the concept of their social program.
The civil engineers and architects thus have an easier time reconciling their demanding jobs and child welfare.
The mini-kindergarten is an original idea of the employees of Arch.Design and with the support of the management they were able to win European Union and Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs funding for their project.
The operational mini-kindergarten is financed through the Operational Programme Human Resources and Employment Policy from funds of the European Social Fund and from the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to this funding (grants amounting to CZK 2.8 million), it was possible to procure the necessary equipment and equipment, and for the duration of 2 years, qualified personnel and operation will be provided.
