The court's mandate is to condemn the old leaders and those who are chiefly responsible for the atrocities, but it is not said whether it will pursue further acts beyond these four cases.
This did little to ease the anxiety in Anlong Veng.
Recent media speculation has focused on Im Chaem, 64 years old, who served as district chief in Manteay Meanchey province during Khmer Rouge rule in the late 1970s.
In 2007 she had told commissioners of the Documentation Center of Cambodia that she had directed the construction of the Trapeang Thma Dam, a project where thousands of forced laborers were probably to die.
On a hot evening, Im Chaem returned from working in the fields to her wooden house on a dirty road outside Anlong Veng.
