As often happens in Cambodia, the young people of Anlong Veng know little about the Khmer Rouge, despite the city's ties to the regime.
Touch Valeak, 19 years, a student at Anlong Veng High School said the new textbook helps students understand an important part of their history.
But his parents reacted skeptically when he brought the book home with him to read.
& quot; My family rejects many parts of the book and the court & quot;, he said.
& quot; You are suspicious because you are not sure how many people are condemned by the court. & quot;
Such resistance makes the reconciliation process complex and complicated, Sok Leang said.
