The USA changes the rules for obtaining a visa
The persons must introduce themselves before their conversation at the Consulate at the Visa Application Service Providers; costs are waiting times are thus shortened.
Starting January 10, 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa are changing at the United States Embassy and at the Consulates.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves to the Visa Application Services (ASC, the first letters in English) before they enter the Consulate.
ASC staff picks up the applicant's biometric data, which is checked by the consulate before the interview.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, these include:
The total cost of visa processing decreases, because it is no longer necessary to pay separately for the appointment arrangement, processing of the visa application, and the transportation service that handles the document.
The applicant will only make a single payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the countervalue to $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for visa with application (including temporary worker visas) and $390 for hand and investor visas.
Those wishing to only renew their visa do not have to make conversation at the consulate. They only have to introduce themselves at the nearest ASC, where they will present their documentation and their fingerprints will be taken.
Since the biometric data is collected in the ASC, the applicants who need a second appointment at the Consulate stay there for less time than before.
Those who apply for the visa at the Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey, and Nuevo Laredo consulates will no longer have to pay the $26 service charge.
Additional information about the new visa application procedure can be found at the following website: http: / / mexico.usembassy.gov / boletines / sp101201 _ Visas-FAQs.html
